SENATE BILL 1162
By Akbari
HOUSE BILL 732
By Camper
AN ACT to amend Tennessee Code Annotated, Title 49,
Chapter 6, relative to assessments.
BE IT ENACTED BY THE GENERAL ASSEMBLY OF THE STATE OF TENNESSEE:
SECTION 1. Tennessee Code Annotated, Title 49, Chapter 6, Part 60, is amended by
adding the following as a new section:
The department of education shall develop or approve a policy developed by an
LEA or public charter school allowing for the retake of a Tennessee comprehensive
assessment program (TCAP) test, including an end-of-course assessment, if the
administration of one (1) or more of the state-mandated TCAP tests is interrupted due to
an act of God or another circumstance beyond the control of the school.
SECTION 2. This act takes effect upon becoming a law, the public welfare requiring it,
and applies to the 2025-2026 school year and each school year thereafter.
